data.name: Font
data.comment: The font to be used to render all text in the product in Windows Vista and later. DO NOT specify more than one font!

data.name: Font.Size.GiantHeading
data.comment: The size of the header text in the Add Weblog wizard and Welcome wizard in Windows Vista and later

data.name: Font.Size.Heading
data.comment: The size of the title in the sign-in dialog in Windows Vista and later

data.name: Font.Size.Large
data.comment: The size of titles in some error dialogs in Windows Vista and later

data.name: Font.Size.Normal
data.comment: The default font size used throughout the product in Windows Vista and later

data.name: Font.Size.PostSplitCaption
data.comment: The size of the font used to draw the 'More...' divider when using the Format | Split Post feature in Windows Vista and later.

data.name: Font.Size.Small
data.comment: The size used for small messages, such as please respect copyright, in Windows Vista and later.

data.name: Font.Size.ToolbarFormatButton
data.comment: The size of the font used to draw the edit toolbar's B(old), I(talic), U(nderline), and S(trikethrough) in Windows Vista and later. THIS SIZE IS IN PIXELS, NOT POINTS! Example: 14.75

data.name: Font.Size.XLarge
data.comment: The size of titles in some error dialogs in Windows Vista and later. Also used for the text that shows an error on the video publish place holder.

data.name: Font.Size.XXLarge
data.comment: The size of panel titles in the Preferences dialog in Windows Vista and later. Also the size of the text used to show the status on the video before publish.

data.name: Sidebar.WidthInPixels
data.comment: The width of the sidebar, in pixels.
